  "title": "Cargo Officer/Bunker Clerk",
  "description": "<h3>Role Overview</h3><p>The Cargo Officer / Bunker Clerk supports bunker operations onboard vessels, ensuring accurate measurements, documentation, and compliance with bunkering standards.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Execute bunker cargo operations onboard bunker tankers.</p></li><li><p>Perform cargo measurements and documentation accurately.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with bunkering standards and procedures.</p></li><li><p>Support shift-based onboard operations.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Minimum 1 year of experience as bunker clerk or cargo officer onboard bunker tankers.</p></li><li><p>Certification in SS600 & TR48 (Basic & Advanced Bunkering Practices).</p></li><li><p>Certification in SS648:2024 (Bunker Mass Flow Metering).</p></li><li><p>Willingness to stay onboard and follow shift schedules.</p></li><li><p>Meticulous, responsible, and effective communicator.</p></li></ul>",
